HEADWORD: Drub
<hw>Drub</hw> <pr>(dr⟦ucr⟧b)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Drubbed</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Drubbing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Cf. Prov. E. <ets>drab</ets> to
beat, Icel. & Sw. <ets>drabba</ets> to hit, beat, Dan.
<ets>dr⟦ae⟧be</ets> to slay, and perh. OE. <ets>drepen</ets> to strike,
kill, AS. <ets>drepan</ets> to strike, G. & D. <ets>freffen</ets> to
hit, touch, Icel. <ets>drepa</ets> to strike, kill.]</ety> <def>To beat
with a stick; to thrash; to cudgel.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Soundly <qex>Drubbed</qex> with a good honest cudgel.</q>
